HEADWORD: meaningless
<hw>meaningless</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>having no meaning; of no
value; <as>as, a <ex>meaningless</ex> endeavor; a <ex>meaningless</ex>
life; a <ex>meaningless</ex> explanation</as>. Opposite of
<ant>meaningful</ant>.</def> [Narrower terms: <stype>insignificant
</stype>; <stype>mindless, unmeaning </stype>;
<stype>nonsense(prenominal), nonsensical </stype>; <stype>pointless,
purposeless </stype>] <see>Also See: <er>insignificant</er>,
<er>unimportant</er>, <er>purposeless</er>,
<er>unimportant</er>.</see>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

